			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While they can solo easy enough as it is using root, mez and charm, the beastlord duo gives them hp buffs, SD, SoW, and paragon, plus extra dps to take down the mobs faster. Anyway I just wanted to share a couple of tips for those who duo with chanters since I often find myself xp'ing with just myself and a chanter.
<br />

<br />
Tip: I use incapacitate, sha's and abolish disease to help the chanter keep control of their pet when it breaks charm. 
<br />

<br />
As soon as the chanter's pet breaks charm I will cast incapacitate on it to get aggro off the chanter.  Then I'll cast slow on the mob to keep it aggro on me and to make sure that it doesn't hit me or the chanter for much if it gets close enough.  In the meantime, the chanter usually casts root, tash and then recharms the mob as their pet. 
<br />

<br />
After the chanter has their pet back, I cast abolish disease on it to cure the sha's slow and we're back to getting xp.
<br />

<br />
Note: I've tried using hobble to get the mob snared but the proc is just not reliable. Your pet also usually doesn't get aggro off of the chanter so that they can get away from the mob long enough to cast and recharm the mob - therefore I don't use hobble for this at all.  Your chanter will probably be dead by the time the proc goes off if you had to rely on this even if your warder is buffed with all the goodies like haste, str, dex, and IoS. lol
<br />

<br />

<br />
(Don't I wish we had root /dream on... Root CLR/9 PAL/22 SHM/14 NEC/34 WIZ/4 ENC/<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=537728" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/briancc/digsigendo.jpg" border="0" /></a>
