				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wish I could give advice but I'm pretty focused at the high end of the game. The good news is that I do have a 65 enchanter and a 65 beastlord <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />  I'll give you some ideas but since I haven't played in the lower levels and lower level zones in so long that I can't give you very specific info.
<br />

<br />
The enchanters role doesn't really change as they level.  Chanters mainly keep the same line/type of spells and they just keep getting improved as they level.
<br />

<br />
Even at lower levels, the enchanter can contribute these types of things to your duo'ing:
<br />

<br />
I'll list the lower level enchanter spells for you...
<br />
- Root and mez mobs (so you can back off and heal or handle adds) (root/mesmerize)
<br />
- Cast a mana regen spell on you (breeze)
<br />
- Debuff the mob (enfeeblement & tashan)
<br />
- Cast melee haste on you (quickness)
<br />
- Charm a mob for their pet to help add dps (charm)
<br />
- Stun the mob (whirl/color flux) 
<br />
- Slow the mob (languid pace)
<br />

<br />
Basically as a beastlord, you will melee the mob with your pet and the chanter will charm a pet and assist you. Buff the chanter with any buffs that you have before you engage to prevent them from dying if a mob hits them since chanters have pretty low AC and HP's. If the mob gets to the chanter, they usually will die pretty quickly so it's your job to prevent this from happening...
<br />

<br />
Just make sure to keep the mob aggro'd on yourself by melee'ing it and casting your combat spells on it to keep it aggro on you. 
<br />

<br />
Overall, the chanter is going to do 3 main things that will make them easy to kill:
<br />
- Cast haste on you
<br />
- Slow the mob
<br />
- Debuff the mob<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=537728" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/briancc/digsigendo.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
